edu.uwm.owyh.jdowrappers

Interface WrapperObject<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - - JDO class
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    OfficeHoursWrapper, PersonWrapper

    public interface WrapperObject<E>
extends java.io.Serializable
     Interface for all JDO wrapper classes. Used to hide the JDO 
 implementation. More importantly, allows control over what is set
 to the JDO's to avoid accidental persistence of bad data.
    Author:
    Vince Maiuri

      • addChildObject

        java.util.List<java.lang.String> addChildObject(java.lang.Object childJDO)
                                                throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        Optional utility method for Parent wrapper classes to set their children fields.
 Allows a hook from child wrapper class to inform the parent wrapper class to set its
 child JDO field. JDO's with no children will not implement this method.
        Parameters:
        childJDO - - Child JDO to set as child of the calling parent object
        Returns:
        A list of any errors that might have occurred while setting the child jdo. If list is
         not empty, then no child was added.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - - If JDO class has no child classes, this method will not
                                         be implemented
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException

      • removeChildObject

        boolean removeChildObject(java.lang.Object childJDO)
                          throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        Optional utility method for Parent wrapper classes to remove child jdo's from child fields.
 Allows a hook from child wrapper class to inform the parent wrapper class to remove Child jdo.
 JDO's with no children will not implement this method.
        Parameters:
        childJDO - - Child JDO to remove from calling parent object
        Returns:
        true if child jdo was removed
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - - If JDO class has no child classes, this method will not
                                         be implemented
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
